- coinbase as of Q2 has 89 billion registered users
- each quarter only 10 million are active
- globally, 200 million people have tried using coinbase
- to get to 1 billion users, we need better blockchains
	1. - too expensive, too slow
	- we’re on dial-ups and we need broadband
	- L2s
	2. - more clear regulation
	- pension and asset funds tell Brian they have 1%. They want to put in 20% but they’re waiting for more clear regulation. (The legal test of what a cryptocurrency is: a commodity, a currency, art, etc)